            <title>[HADOOP-10455] When there is an exception, ipc.Server should first check whether it is an terse exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10455</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ipc.Server allows application servers to define terse exceptions; see Server.addTerseExceptions.  For terse exception, it only prints a short message but not the stack trace.  However, if an exception is both RuntimeException and terse exception, it still prints out the stack trace of the exception.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
